Japan’s Topix Core 30 Index Tumbles to Record Low After S&P Cuts

-- B y   A k i k o   I k e d a   a n d   S a t o s h i   K a w a n o
-- 
2011-08-09T00:08:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/japan-s-topix-core-30-index-tumbles-to-record-low-after-s-p-cuts.html
Japan ’s Topix Core 30 Index of the
nation’s largest stocks declined for a sixth day, dropping to a
record low, after  Standard & Poor’s  cut credit ratings for U.S.-
sponsored mortgage finance companies.  The gauge plunged 3.5 percent to 395.22 as of 9:04 a.m. in
 Tokyo , its lowest level since the start of the index in April
1998.  To contact the reporters on the story:
Akiko Ikeda in Tokyo at 
 iakiko@bloomberg.net ;
Satoshi Kawano in Tokyo at 
 skawano1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
